&nbsp;
< blockquote
In 2019, Ivanov was included in the ranking of richer security officials, compiled by Forbes magazine, who estimated the income of his family in 2018 to 136,7 million rubles (over 1.3 million euros)
</blockquote
&nbsp;
Subject to US and EU sanctions, Ivanov was at the center of several journalistic investigations. According to an investigation published in 2022 by the opponent's team <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-03-08/navalny-media-putin-tratto-scambio-fino-25626568/">Aleksei Navalny</a>, who died in prison in February, the then wife of the vice-minister, Svetlana Ivano A source of Forbes to the Ministry of Defence has speculated that the detention of the deputy minister could fall into a wider "purge" which should anticipate Shoigu's departure from the ministry.
