The arrests of high-profile government officials are rare in Russia and are usually the result of internal political struggles. The large sums earmarked for the Ukrainian offensive gave officials new opportunities to enrich themselves with untransparent contracts. Russian military bloggers and Telegram channels linked to Wagner's mercenary company have long criticized Shoigu's offensive management, immediately focusing on Ivanov's bond with the contested minister. The former head of Wagner, Evgheny Prigozhin, had accused Shoigu and other officials of the Ministry of Defence of Corruption and Incompetence before his mysterious death last year.
