"I will fix this bill and address myself to the American people as soon as they arrive on my desk tomorrow, so we can start sending weapons and equipment to Ukraine this week," Biden said, adding that the approval of the bill shows that America is "resolutely in favor of Ukraine". democracy and freedom, and against tyranny and oppression."
&nbsp;
<h2>Kiev, killed 461 thousand Russian soldiers from the beginning of the invasion
Russia lost 461,940 soldiers in Ukraine from the beginning of its large-scale invasion on 24 February 2022. That's what the major state of the Ukrainian armed forces says. The number includes 880 victims suffered by Russian forces only in yesterday's day, according to Kiev.<br> According to the figures provided by the Ukrainian army reported by the Kiev press, Russia also lost 7,242 tanks, 13,928 armoured vehicles, 15,892 vehicles and fuel tanks, 11,808 artillery systems, 1.048 multi-launch rocket systems, 771 aircraft defense systems
&nbsp;
<h2>Putin, protect traditional values to strengthen sovereignty ></h2>
Conservation and protection of traditional spiritual and moral values is the most important condition for strengthening the sovereignty and security of states. The Russian President, Vladimir Putin, said this in a video message to participants at the 12th International Meeting of High Representatives in office for security issues. "As evidenced by the historical experience - said Putin according to Ria Novosti - the countries that preserve the national identity and the originality of their people, honor the memory of their ancestors and at the same time respect the other cultures and traditions, develop in a coherent and independent way". According to the Russian agency, this approach "is particularly important today, when a multipolar world order is being formed and global power balances are gradually changing in favour of the world majority, when new development centers are actively strengthening". &nbsp;

